<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-10-22T19:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-10-22T19:36:00-05:00" n="934" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d934">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/13570.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Vice Consul <persName type="from">Silliman</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Mexico City</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-10-22T18:00:00-06:36">
                                    <hi rend="italic">October 22, 1914, 6 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Carranza has not heard further from Convention regarding Vera Cruz.
                            Regardless of Convention, his reply to American Government through
                            Brazilian Minister, who on October 8 communicated my telegram of 7th, 5
                            p.m., to Fabela, will be to the effect that he considers it inexpedient
                            for him to issue such a statement as the Department desires. At the same
                            time he says that no one will be molested on account of service rendered
                            Americans and no back duties or taxes will be collected.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Silliman</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>